# Token service errors (7000–7099)
E7000 = The grant_type is not supported.
E7001 = The client_id is required.
E7002 = An unexpected error occurred while looking up the authorization code.
E7003 = The authorization code was not found.
E7004 = The authorization code does not belong to the authenticated client.
E7005 = The authorization code is no longer valid.
E7006 = An unexpected error occurred while reading the authorization code.
E7007 = The redirect_uri does not match the authorization code.
E7008 = The code_verifier is required.
E7009 = An unexpected error occurred due to a data integrity issue.
E7010 = An unexpected error occurred while looking up the user.
E7011 = The user associated with the authorization code was not found.
E7012 = An unexpected error occurred while revoking the authorization code.
E7013 = An unexpected error occurred while looking up the refresh token.
E7014 = The refresh token was not found.
E7015 = The refresh token is no longer valid.
E7016 = An unexpected error occurred while reading the refresh token.
E7017 = The refresh token is missing the subject claim.
E7018 = The refresh token is missing the token_use claim.
E7019 = The refresh token type is invalid.
E7020 = The refresh token does not belong to the authenticated client.
E7021 = The refresh token subject is not a valid identifier.
E7022 = The user associated with the refresh token was not found.
E7023 = An unexpected error occurred while revoking the refresh token.
E7024 = An unexpected error occurred while loading signing keys.
E7025 = No signing key is available. Please contact your administrator.
E7026 = The client_id is not a valid identifier.
E7027 = The client was not found.
E7028 = An unexpected error occurred while looking up the client.
E7029 = An unexpected error occurred while looking up client credentials.
E7030 = The client credentials are invalid.
E7031 = Client authentication is required.
E7032 = The client assertion is missing the issuer claim.
E7033 = The client assertion is missing the subject claim.
E7034 = The client assertion issuer and subject must equal the client_id.
E7035 = The client assertion audience does not include the issuer.
E7036 = The client assertion has expired.
E7037 = The client assertion is not yet valid.
E7038 = The client assertion JWT header is invalid.
E7039 = The client assertion signature could not be verified.
E7040 = The client assertion algorithm is not supported.
E7041 = The client assertion key is invalid.
E7042 = The refresh token signature could not be verified.
E7043 = An unexpected error occurred while signing the access token.
E7044 = An unexpected error occurred while signing the ID token.
E7045 = An unexpected error occurred while signing the refresh token.
E7046 = An unexpected error occurred while saving the refresh token.
E7047 = An unexpected error occurred while saving the refresh token.
E7048 = The code_challenge_method is not supported.
E7049 = The code_verifier does not match the code_challenge.
